President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Mississippi due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from May 1-2, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Affected individuals in certain counties will have access to grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other assistance programs. Federal funding will also be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities, as well as for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Michael Bolch has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance online or by phone.